Taita Taveta leaders have urged the state to issue ID cards to Tanzanian women married to Kenyans.Woman representative hopeful Rozina Kisochi on Tuesday said she will petition the National Assembly to pass legislation ensuring all women legally married to Kenyans get IDs.She spoke to the Star on the phone.Kisochi said lack of IDs has marginalised the women. They have to bend very low to get loans in empowerment groups. Worse still, they cannot access bank loans, she said.Kisochi is a nominated MCA in the Taita Taveta assembly. She represents people living with disability. The MCA said more than 1,000 women in Taveta do not have IDs and need them to get voter s cards.